<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="998" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1059,1113,1223]" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<emphasis box="[473,564,1113,1134]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">Ampleris</emphasis>
OPITZ and its 7 previously described species were made available in 2016 (
<bibRefCitation author="OPITZ W" box="[473,599,1142,1164]" pageId="39" pageNumber="998" pagination="260 - 283" refId="ref53690" refString="OPITZ W. (2016): Taxonomy of the New World Pseudichnea complex (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Peloniinae). - Canadian Entomologist 148: 260 - 283." type="journal article" year="2016">OPITZ 2016</bibRefCitation>
). That work included a key to species. The available 
<emphasis box="[251,397,1171,1193]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">Ampleris jatai</emphasis>
specimen keys out to 
<emphasis box="[636,728,1172,1193]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">A. orosis</emphasis>
OPITZ, from which the 
<emphasis box="[981,1059,1172,1193]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">A. jatai</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[151,240,1201,1223]" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">holotype</typeStatus>
differs by showing shorter and wider capitular antennomeres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="998" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1059,1238,1553]" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 
<quantity box="[516,597,1238,1260]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="39" pageNumber="998" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
; width 1.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[895,980,1238,1260]" captionStart="Figs 318-321" captionStartId="107.[151,191,1519,1541]" captionTargetBox="[156,1063,202,1502]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[153,1063,192,1502]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="Figs 318-321: Habitus; (318) Ampleris ituituba; (319) A. jatai (320) Cregya arima; (321) C. biguttula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746820/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">Fig. 319</figureCitation>
. Color: Clypeus and lower frons testaceous, upper frons and epicranium brown, except epicranium with narrow testaceous streak at middle; gena testaceous; antenna brown; prothorax bicolored, venter testaceous; pronotum bicolored, disc broadly brown at sides, narrowly testaceous at middle, testaceous region laden with yellow setae; pterothorax, elytra, legs, and abdomen piceous. Head: Cranium coarsely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation box="[974,1050,1385,1407]" captionStart="Figs 61-91" captionStartId="73.[151,191,1343,1365]" captionTargetBox="[151,1033,198,1310]" captionTargetId="figure@73.[151,1059,198,1328]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="Figs 61-91: Antennae; (61) Madoniella muralla; (62) M. nota; (63) M. acicula; (64) M. aspera; (65) M. baja; (66) M. delta; (67) Amboakis bermejo; (68) Pujoliclerus variolus; (69) Megatrachys irrasis; (70) Cregya arima; (71) Nelsopelonium aspikelum; (72) Cregya vicosa; (73) Pujoliclerus abditus; (74) P. dexus; (75) Cregya triguttula; (76) Pyticeroides brevitubulus; (77) Pujoliclerus lasiosus; (78) Cregya biguttula; (79) Sirpa acara; (80) Parapelonides naranjo; (81) Cregya livida; (82) Amboakis collucoatis; (83) Ampleris jatai; (84) Megaphloeus yasuni; (85) Pelonium implacide, male; (86) Epiphloeus prolixicornus; (87) Pelonium implacide, female; (88) Epiphloeus mantillerii; (89) Amboakis mitaraka; (90) Ellipotoma makrosa; (91) Cregya maura." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746752/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres transverse, very setose, capitular antennomeres oblong; eyes small, coarsely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 10/17). Thorax: Pronotal disc (
<figureCitation box="[209,298,1473,1495]" captionStart="Figs 179-193" captionStartId="81.[151,191,1359,1381]" captionTargetBox="[167,1032,201,1342]" captionTargetId="figure@81.[152,1058,201,1346]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="Figs 179-193: Pronota; 179) Phonius versus; (180) Perilypus arsus; (181) A. nodus; (182) Pyticara frontegalba; (183) Pelonium implacide; (184) Neorthoplera quintana; (185) Perilypus virgulatus; (186) P. alpinus; (187) Amboakis expandosa; (188) Ampleris jatai; (189) Megaphloeus jasuni; (190) Amboakis bermejo (191) Madoniella delta; (192) Megaphloeus imparilus; (193) Pyticeroides brevitubulus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746768/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">Fig. 188</figureCitation>
) coarsely punctate, slightly oblong (PW/PL 40/43); lateral tubercle well developed; elytral asetiferous punctures substriate (EL/EW 165/35). Abdomen: Pygidium subquadrate/scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[649,740,1531,1553]" captionStart="Figs 231-236" captionStartId="88.[151,191,1287,1309]" captionTargetBox="[156,1064,199,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@88.[156,1064,199,1273]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="Figs 231-236: Aedeagi; (231) Neorthopleura quintana; (232) N. thomasi; (233) N. turnbowi; (234) Ampleris cacuminis; (235) A. itaituba; (236) A. jatai." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746782" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746782/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="998">Fig. 236.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
